---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: 'PRF Microneedling | D-Essence Wellness',
  description:
    'Microneedling paired with platelet-rich fibrin (PRF) to support collagen, refine texture, soften scars, and enhance tone with a regenerative approach and minimal downtime.',
  canonical: '/services/prf-microneedling/',
  type: 'website',
  jsonLd: [
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'Service',
      name: 'PRF Microneedling',
      serviceType: 'Microneedling with Platelet-Rich Fibrin',
      areaServed: 'New Windsor, New York',
      provider: {
        '@type': 'MedicalBusiness',
        name: 'D-Essence Wellness',
        address: {
          '@type': 'PostalAddress',
          streetAddress: '871 Blooming Grove Turnpike Suite 102',
          addressLocality: 'New Windsor',
          addressRegion: 'NY',
          postalCode: '12553',
          addressCountry: 'US'
        }
      },
      url: 'https://dessencewellness.com/services/prf-microneedling/'
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo}>
  <!-- ===== HERO (dark) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 text-white">
    <div class="container pt-28 pb-10 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">
        <span>Services</span><span class="opacity-40">•</span><span>Advanced Skin Care</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">PRF Microneedling</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/80">
        A regenerative take on microneedling. Platelet-rich fibrin delivers growth factors through fresh
        microchannels to support collagen, refine texture, and promote an even, luminous tone.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-sm">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Series</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">3–4 sessions</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Spacing</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Every 4–6 weeks</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Areas</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Face, eyes, neck, hands</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Downtime</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">1–3 days redness</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CONTENT (white) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-white text-neutral-900">
    <div class="container py-12 sm:py-14">

      <!-- Overview -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            PRF stands for platelet-rich fibrin—a fibrin matrix prepared from your own blood without added
            anticoagulants. The matrix naturally traps platelets, white blood cells, and growth factors to
            release them gradually. When combined with microneedling, PRF is layered over freshly created
            microchannels to encourage collagen synthesis and tissue repair with a restorative, skin-health-first approach.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Targets include texture and tone, early lines, acne scarring, and dullness. PRF microneedling is also
            suitable for delicate areas like the peri-orbital region, neck, and hands where a gentler regenerative
            stimulus is preferred.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Key benefits</h3>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Improves texture, tone, luminosity, and uniformity
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Softens fine lines and superficial wrinkles
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Helps reduce the look of acne scars and surface irregularities
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Supports long-term collagen and tissue regeneration
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Autologous product with minimal risk of immune reaction
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-neutral-500">
              Individual outcomes vary; not all concerns respond equally. Your clinician will tailor a plan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What to expect -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What to expect</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            After a medical and skin assessment, a small blood draw is collected and centrifuged to create a PRF matrix.
            A topical anesthetic keeps you comfortable while the device makes depth-controlled passes. PRF is applied
            immediately over the microchannels to enhance penetration and support repair.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">The session</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li>Topical numbing as needed</li>
                <li>Microneedling with tailored depths by area</li>
                <li>Immediate application of PRF over treated skin</li>
                <li>Typical time: ~30–60 minutes depending on areas</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">Timeline</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li>Day 0: redness, warmth, or tightness is common</li>
                <li>Days 1–3: mild swelling; early glow may appear</li>
                <li>Weeks 1–4: visible gains in texture and uniformity</li>
                <li>Ongoing: collagen remodeling over subsequent weeks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5 sm:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">Series planning</div>
              <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                Most plans include 3–4 sessions spaced every 4–6 weeks, with maintenance as needed.
                We’ll align the protocol with your goals, skin type, and lifestyle.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Aftercare -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Aftercare</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Avoid rubbing, massaging, or picking for at least 24 hours.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Gentle cleanser, tepid water, and non-irritating hydrators only.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Skip heavy makeup on day one; reintroduce as advised.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Avoid intense exercise, steam, or sauna for 24–48 hours.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Daily SPF; limit direct sun while skin settles.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Avoid strong actives (retinoids, strong acids) for ~7–10 days.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Safety & Risks -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Safety & risks</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Common, temporary effects</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Redness, mild swelling, warmth or tightness</li>
              <li>Pinpoint bleeding or small bruises</li>
              <li>Transient sensitivity as skin renews</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Precautions & contraindications</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Active infection, inflamed acne, eczema/psoriasis flare, open wounds</li>
              <li>Recent isotretinoin or aggressive procedures—timing matters</li>
              <li>Bleeding disorders or anticoagulants—requires evaluation</li>
              <li>History of keloids or poor healing—use caution</li>
              <li>Pregnancy or breastfeeding—typically deferred</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-neutral-500">
          Educational information only; not medical advice. Candidacy and technique are determined by your clinician.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">FAQ</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">How many sessions will I need?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Most patients plan 3–4 sessions every 4–6 weeks, with maintenance based on goals and response.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">When will I see results?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Early improvements can appear within the first few weeks; more visible changes develop as collagen remodels.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Is it painful?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Topical numbing is used to keep you comfortable. Expect mild redness or tightness for a day or two.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">How is PRF different from PRP?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              PRF is processed without anticoagulants, creating a fibrin matrix that gradually releases growth factors.
              Many patients appreciate the regenerative feel and autologous, minimal-additive approach.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
            Curious whether PRF or PRP is the better fit for your goals? We’ll help you decide with a skin-health plan.
          </div>
          <a href="/contact-us/" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-neutral-900 text-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm hover:bg-neutral-800 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-neutral-300">
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
